.SH COMMON FAILURES
.IP \(bu 2
Running tests without scans and assuming the environment is healthy.
.IP \(bu 2
Treating vulnerability output as self\-explanatory without checking the
related report artifacts or task context.
.IP \(bu 2
Refreshing a published image base without rebuilding and rescanning the
published image set.
.SH GUIDANCE
.IP \(bu 2
Security checks belong in the normal development loop.
.IP \(bu 2
Use structured artifacts when available.
.IP \(bu 2
Prefer the maintainer\-container workflow over host\-local shortcuts.
.IP \(bu 2
Prefer the official Dev Containers CLI maintainer lane over raw host
shell execution.
.IP \(bu 2
Prefer the published GHCR maintainer image over rebuilding the
maintainer image on the host.
.IP \(bu 2
For Python package audits, review \f[CR]security\-scan\-policy.toml\f[R]
before changing failure behavior.
.IP \(bu 2
Use that policy to decide which severities hard\-fail, whether no\-fix
advisories may continue, and whether a specific advisory has a temporary
accepted override.
.IP \(bu 2
For published images, resolve and pin base digests before rebuilding and
rescanning the published image set.
.IP \(bu 2
Classify published\-image scan findings into two buckets:
.RS 2
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]repo\-fixable\f[R]: stale base images, stale distro packages,
stale pinned tool versions, or missing checksum and refresh behavior
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]upstream residual\f[R]: findings that remain in the latest
upstream\-supported released binary for a third\-party tool the
repository installs
.RE
.IP \(bu 2
Fix all \f[CR]repo\-fixable\f[R] findings first.
.IP \(bu 2
Record \f[CR]upstream residual\f[R] findings in the residual\-risk
artifacts and keep the upstream vendor binary rather than privately
rebuilding it only to clear the scanner output.
.IP \(bu 2
Treat a private rebuild of a third\-party security tool as an exception
that requires explicit human direction.
